# Profile landing conventions

- Vite + Alpine.js + [vite-plugin-handlebars](https://www.npmjs.com/package/vite-plugin-handlebars) + colocated components. No backend. Publish `dist/` via GitHub Actions.
- Content: `src/shared/data/profile.js`. Prefer editing that file for copy and links.
- Components: `src/components/<section>/` (HTML + CSS + JS `index.js`); include as `{{> section/name }}`.
- Shared foundation: `src/shared/{styles,data,i18n,lib}/`.
- i18n locales: `src/shared/i18n/locales/` (`ru` `uk` `en` `es` `de` `zh` `ja`). Spoken langs in `profile.spokenLanguages`.
- Follow `DESIGN.md`: Steam dark palette, Exo 2 + Source Sans 3.
- Initial UI locale follows the browser (`navigator.languages`), then English; saved preference wins. `document.documentElement.lang` follows the switcher.
- `vite.config.js` `base` must match the Pages path (`/profile/` for this repo).
- Single Alpine root `profilePage` composed in `src/app/profile-page.js` — do not add a second framework or N `x-data` islands.
- Do not commit `node_modules/` or `dist/`.
- Versioning: keep `package.json` `version` and `CHANGELOG.md` in sync (SemVer / Keep a Changelog). See `AGENTS.md`.
- Preserve accessibility (skip link, focus-visible, reduced motion, x-cloak).
- Do not use Handlebars `{{ }}` for Alpine text binding — keep `x-text` / `:attr`.
